TITLE: Simple snowball cookies for Christmas: Try the recipe
SUMMARY: Enjoy a sweet and festive treat this Christmas season with these delicious snowball cookies that can be paired with coffee or a rich cup of hot cocoa.

TITLE: US scientists produce first successful nuclear fusion reaction resulting in net energy gain
SUMMARY: Energy officials announced Tuesday that scientists at a California laboratory had produced the first successful nuclear fusion reaction resulting in net energy gain.

TITLE: Indian, Chinese soldiers clash in disputed border region, injuries reported on both sides
SUMMARY: Indian and Chinese troops were involved in a violent clash in a disputed border region on Friday that reportedly resulted in several injuries on both sides.

TITLE: Youngkin sets special election to fill Rep. McEachin's seat
SUMMARY: Following the death of late Democratic Rep. A. Donald McEachin, Virginia Governor Glenn Youngkin is setting a special election in order to fill the 4th Congressional seat.

TITLE: West Virginia seeks to expand dilapidated buildings program
SUMMARY: West Virginia issued a survey asking leaders to expand a dilapidated buildings program. The survey will help officials decide which communities will receive funding.

TITLE: Feeding America CEO asks community to help others amid today's high inflation
SUMMARY: Feeding America's CEO Claire Babineaux-Fontenot joined "Fox & Friends" on Tuesday to discuss the impact that high inflation has had on the organization and those in the community.

TITLE: Colorado River Water Users Association to hold Las Vegas conference amid drought crisis
SUMMARY: Officials from California, Colorado, New Mexico, Utah, Wyoming, Arizona and Nevada will convene to address how states can reduce its Colorado River water consumption.

TITLE: White Florida officer accused of shoving Black woman acquitted of battery charge
SUMMARY: A white Florida police officer was acquitted for the shoving of a Black woman during a protest more than two years ago. The officer's misdemeanor was punishable by up to a year.

TITLE: Ahead of Christmas, Home Depot employees track down customer who dropped $700 cash: 'Positivity and kindness'
SUMMARY: A pair of Home Depot employees in Tennessee were able to locate the owner of a cash-filled envelope that was accidentally dropped in the store during the holiday season.

TITLE: Ken DeLand disappearance in France shines light on Europe's 'abolished' borders travel zone
SUMMARY: The disappearance of Ken DeLand while studying abroad in France has pointed to Europe's Schengen zone where travelers aren't required to present passports, identification.
